column5: Next saturday is the big day!  So were is everyone heading?  I'll be out on Pigeon lake, been musky huntin that lake for the last 5 years or so now.  Can't wait!  got all the hooks sharp and ready to go!
I'll be up there the following Wednesday night to hunt some Esox, and to take part in the Toronto Chapter(Muskies Canada) Outing on Saturday!!! Can't wait!

I'm going in the kayak so I won't know where until either the night before or morning I leave. Have to see how hard the wind is blowing and what direction before I pick a launch spot. I have many to choose from so, no matter what the wind is doing, I'll be in the Kawarthas somewhere. Good luck to all.

I'll be out for a few hours in the evening after work over the weekend, but my opener happens on the following wed/thurs. I'll be out on the kawartha's pounding the water both days, all day. Can't friggen wait!!!!!  Sinker
Planning to get out mid week next week, gotta work opener. Might try several lakes in the next week or so. A chuckin bucks I will go...weeeeeee.
I'm hoping to be on the water by 7. It's like being a kid and waiting for Christmas, It can't come soon enough.

We'll probably be on the water for first light, going to try a little further south this year, usually fish the north end but gonna try down by grenadier island and gannons narrows, atleast for the morning anyways. Can't freakin' wait!
I will be fishing a lake for muskie and walleye on the weekend
The forecast is for light rain and 25K winds...Make sure your loved ones are wearing PFD's!!! I will have clients on Lower Buckhorn, and I won't let then eat the future of fishing...HAHAHA
Pigeon?? Can't remember tha last time I caught "a single" Lunge out there.  Meely
Might try Scugog from shore with some smaller baits for smaller Musky for awhile. Then, I'll get out another rod and go for some more Perch!  If your at Scugog say hi
Cameron Lake for a few. Then back to Pics.
hitting up Scugog , have seen plenty of the toothy critters already ! cant wait !
Wow, lots of guys going to Pigeon!!
Forecast is looking better now, mainly sunny, 17c and 10k W winds.  Fairly stable weather leading up to it too.....nice.
Won't be out on the weekend, but will head out midway through next week.. a little closer to home.
Took the week off.  Starting on Head Lake then off to G Bay.
gbay is closed for muskie till last saturday in june.  i'd rebook your holiday.  we'll be out,.. but not on the kawarthas.
Thanks Raf! Good to know. The plans must go on, maybe Stony lake instead.
For the Musky folks Sunday is also the full moon period for June, make sure you have all your proper release tools on board, for a quick and safe release for the fish and you.   Good luck yall
Good luck to all, remember to have these!      And most importantly, do this!    As a friend of mine says, "Be nice to the Ladies"
